Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:27.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,热爱软件工程技术。 \N {\rENG} love the craft of software engineering.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在过去的几年里，我一直致力于使用网络技术构建现代、高品质的 \N {\rENG} For the past few years, I've been on a journey to build a modern, high quality
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.00,0:00:34.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,音乐应用程序。 \N {\rENG} music app using web technologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.00,0:00:39.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这样做的过程中，我陷入了本地第一软件的困境。 \N {\rENG} And in doing so, I've been falling down the rabbit hole of local first software.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.00,0:00:42.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个播客是邀请您加入我的旅程。 \N {\rENG} This podcast is your invitation to join me on that journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.00,0:00:47.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在本期节目中，我将采访 Peter van Hardenberg，他帮助 \N {\rENG} In this inaugural episode, I'm speaking to Peter van Hardenberg, who helped to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.00,0:00:50.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,创造并推广了“本地优先”一词。 \N {\rENG} coin and popularize the term Local First.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:53.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,作为 Ink & Switch研究实验室的主任，他在十年的大部分时间里一直处于 \N {\rENG} As the director of the Ink & Switch Research Lab, he's been on
