Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.00,0:01:19.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在是我对彼得的采访。 \N {\rENG} And now my interview with Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.00,0:01:21.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你好，欢迎彼得。 非常 \N {\rENG} Hello, welcome Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.00,0:01:26.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,感谢您今天能和我一起开始这个新的播客。 \N {\rENG} Thank you so much for making it today to kick off this new podcast with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.00,0:01:28.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,那么你介意介绍一下自己吗？ \N {\rENG} So would you mind introducing yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:29.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的。 大家 \N {\rENG} Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.00,0:01:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,好，我叫彼得·范·哈登伯格。 \N {\rENG} Hi, my name is Peter Van Hardenberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.00,0:01:34.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是Ink & Switch 研究实验室的主任。 \N {\rENG} I am the director of Ink & Switch Research Labs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.00,0:01:37.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们是一个独立的工业研究实验室，研究 \N {\rENG} We're an independent industrial research lab studying the future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.00,0:01:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,计算和思维工具的未来。 \N {\rENG} of computing and tools for thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.00,0:01:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,惊人的。 \N {\rENG} Awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.00,0:01:43.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,彼得和我认识已经有一段时间了。 \N {\rENG} Peter and I have known us for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.00,0:01:48.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,当时，Peter 刚刚结束他在 Heroku 的最后一章， \N {\rENG} Back then, Peter, has been just closing up his last chapter at Heroku
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:50.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一直是 Heroku 的忠实粉丝。 \N {\rENG} which I've been always a big fan of.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:58.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,Peter 现在找到了致力于本地优先并定义本地优先的方法。 \N {\rENG} Peter found his way now working on local first and defining what local first is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.00,0:02:02.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在深入探讨之前，是什么让您首先选择本地化？ \N {\rENG} Before going into it, what has led you to local first?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.00,0:02:04.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，我的意思是，显然这有点背离，对吧？ \N {\rENG} Yeah, I mean, obviously it's a bit of a departure, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.00,0:02:07.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像，我在这里构建一个平台即服务。 \N {\rENG} Like, here I was building a platform as a service.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.00,0:02:12.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,您知道，Heroku，对于那些不知道的人来说，基本上是一个主机， \N {\rENG} You know, Heroku, for those who don't know, is a, basically a host
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.00,0:02:15.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,主要是在它开始用于 Rubyon Rails 应用程序时，但随着 \N {\rENG} Primarily when it started for Ruby on Rails applications, but over
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:17.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,时间的推移几乎可以用于所有内容。 \N {\rENG} time for pretty much everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.00,0:02:20.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,Heroku 背后的想法是，你可以在你的机器上构建一个应用程序， \N {\rENG} And the idea behind Heroku is that you could build an app on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.00,0:02:22.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后推送它。 \N {\rENG} your machine and then push it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:26.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,对于持续交付系统，它将把它放在云中，并且 \N {\rENG} To a continuous delivery system, and it would put it live in the cloud, and there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:30.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,今天还有其他类似的系统，您可以想象它，如您所知，原始 Netlify \N {\rENG} are other systems like that today, you can imagine it as you know, proto Netlify
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:35.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,或早期的容器化云。 \N {\rENG} or early kind of, containerized cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.00,0:02:38.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，从试图让每个人的 \N {\rENG} Yeah, and it is a bit of a departure to go from trying to get everybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:41.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,应用程序在云中运行到告诉人们也许他们应该 \N {\rENG} apps running in the cloud to telling people that maybe they should
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.00,0:02:44.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在自己的计算机上运行它们，这有点背离。 \N {\rENG} just run them on their computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.00,0:02:47.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我想我真的应该解释一下我们是如何到达那里的。 \N {\rENG} So I guess I should really explain how we got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.00,0:02:50.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得对我来说。 \N {\rENG} I think for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.00,0:02:57.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想讲一个关于在旧金山乘坐火车和地铁的故事。 \N {\rENG} I'd like to tell a story about riding the train in San Francisco, the subway there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.00,0:03:00.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的朋友们一直在开发一款名为 Rdio 的音乐应用程序，它是 \N {\rENG} And my friends had been working on a music app called Rdio which was
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.00,0:03:02.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,Spotify 的竞争对手。 \N {\rENG} sort of a competitor to Spotify.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.00,0:03:03.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们已经不在身边了。 \N {\rENG} They're not around anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:08.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道，当我乘坐这趟火车时，当火车在地面上时，我一直 \N {\rENG} And you know, as I was riding on this train, I had been listening
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:11.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在在线模式下听音乐。 \N {\rENG} to music in the online mode when the train was above ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:15.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后当我们进入隧道时，音乐就停止了。 \N {\rENG} And then when we went into the tunnel, the music would just stop working.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.00,0:03:17.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这真的让 \N {\rENG} And it was really...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.00,0:03:22.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我感到不安，因为我无法返回，甚至无法再听我已经 \N {\rENG} upsetting to me because like I couldn't go back and even listen to songs I'd already
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:27.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,听过的歌曲，或者无法滚动浏览我的播放列表，因为我没有处于 \N {\rENG} listened to or like scroll through the playlists that I had because I wasn't in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:35.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,离线模式，而我只记得 有这种感觉，就像我们真的搞砸了， \N {\rENG} offline mode and I just remember having this feeling like we've really blown it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.00,0:03:39.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们已经把软件从这个东西变成了你可以拥有的东西，就像他们称之为 \N {\rENG} we've turned software from this thing that you can just have like they call it an
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.00,0:03:43.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,信息商品一样，这意味着就像你知道复制它 \N {\rENG} informational good that means that like you know the marginal cost of copying it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.00,0:03:47.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,并使用它的边际成本为零一样，就是这样 这个想法是，类似的软件已经从 \N {\rENG} and using it as zero it's just it was this idea that like software had gone from this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:51.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,任何人都可以拥有副本的东西变成了甚至在火车上都无法使用的东西， \N {\rENG} thing that anyone could have a copy of To a thing that didn't even work on the train
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.00,0:03:53.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为我真的没有这个应用程序。 \N {\rENG} because I didn't really have the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:57.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,尽管我手里的数据就在我面前的屏幕上，在 \N {\rENG} Even though I'd had the data in my hand on my screen in front of me, in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:04:01.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的耳朵里听着，但不知怎的，在 \N {\rENG} my ears listening to it, somehow it had just completely evaporated in the time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:02.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,火车进入隧道的时间里，它就完全消失了。 \N {\rENG} it took a train to go into a tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.00,0:04:03.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,正确的。 \N {\rENG} right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.00,0:04:06.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,坐火车可不是那么回事。 就 \N {\rENG} And riding a train is not this out there thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.00,0:04:08.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,好像这就是日常的事情一样。 \N {\rENG} It's like this is a daily thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.00,0:04:09.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，这是我每天的通勤。 \N {\rENG} Yeah, is my daily commute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:12.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,而且，你知道，有人说，哦，是的，你知道， \N {\rENG} And, you know, there are people out there who say, Oh, yeah, you know, the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.00,0:04:16.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,下周互联网将无处不在，你最近坐过地铁吗？ \N {\rENG} Internet's going to be everywhere next week, and have you taken a subway lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.00,0:04:20.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道，就像，都在大城市，对吧？ \N {\rENG} You know, and like, both in big cities, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.00,0:04:22.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你有这个问题，而且在更多的农村社区也有，对吗？ \N {\rENG} You have this problem, but also in more rural communities, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.00,0:04:26.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,有很多地方没有互联网，或者互联网很慢。 \N {\rENG} There's lots of places where there's no Internet, or the Internet is slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.00,0:04:28.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你甚至可以在有互联网的地方，对吧？ \N {\rENG} And you can even be in places where there is Internet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.00,0:04:32.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,但冰箱旁边的手机接收信号不太好， \N {\rENG} But your cell phone reception isn't great next to the fridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:33.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者 Wi-Fi 信号中断。 \N {\rENG} or your Wi Fi has a cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.00,0:04:37.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,每天当我想离开家时都会遇到这种情况， \N {\rENG} Faced this every day when I'm just like leaving the house and there's just this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.00,0:04:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,wifi 就会停止响应。 \N {\rENG} little gap of the wifi stops responding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.00,0:04:44.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,有一点信号，我的应用程序就无法正常工作了。 \N {\rENG} There's a little bit of signal and my apps just don't work properly anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.00,0:04:46.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，一切都被锁定了。 \N {\rENG} Yeah, everything kind of locks up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.00,0:04:50.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的手机只是一块小黑砖，没有良好的 Wi-Fi 连接。 \N {\rENG} Your phone is just a little black brick without a good Wi Fi connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.00,0:04:53.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这让我开始思考，为什么我们要按照 \N {\rENG} And so that got me thinking, like, well, why do we build
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.00,0:04:54.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们的方式来构建东西？ \N {\rENG} things the way we build them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.00,0:04:57.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我认为，某种程度上的答案就是，你 \N {\rENG} And the answer to some extent, I think, was just that, you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.00,0:04:59.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道，我们告诉人们这样做。 \N {\rENG} know, we told people to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.00,0:04:59.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,正确的。 \N {\rENG} Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.00,0:05:03.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们让构建云应用程序变得容易，然后每个人都这样做了。 \N {\rENG} We made it easy to build apps for the cloud, and then everybody did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.00,0:05:03.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的。 \N {\rENG} Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.00,0:05:07.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，所以在 Heroku，我主要从事数据服务工作。 \N {\rENG} Yeah, and so at Heroku, I had worked on our data services mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.00,0:05:09.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就是我们的 Postgres 服务。 \N {\rENG} That was our Postgres service.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.00,0:05:13.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我开始思考问题的根源在于 \N {\rENG} And I started thinking about how really the problem is that the data
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:18.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,应用程序的数据实际上并不存在于您的设备上。 \N {\rENG} that you have for your application doesn't actually live on your device.
