Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.00,0:12:02.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为我们无法回去查看它们的记录 ，他们迷路了。 \N {\rENG} because We can't go back and look at the records from them, they were lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.00,0:12:06.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,同样，我们已经建立了一个技术的黑暗时代。 \N {\rENG} And so similarly, we have built a dark age for technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.00,0:12:09.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是说不好，有很多很棒的东西，但是 \N {\rENG} Not that it's bad, there are a lot of things that are great, but that there
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.00,0:12:12.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这里不会有我们工作的记录，对吧？ \N {\rENG} won't be a record of our work here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.00,0:12:14.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像你和我正在构建的东西， \N {\rENG} Like the things that you and I are building, the work that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.00,0:12:18.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在 Heroku 所做的工作，我们在那里制作和发布的应用程序。 \N {\rENG} I did at Heroku, the apps that we've made and put out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:23.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为它们不是，它们不存在于它们运行的​​一组服务器之外 \N {\rENG} Because they're not, they don't exist outside of the one set of servers they
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.00,0:12:28.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,，你知道，当它们离线时，它们就永远消失了。 \N {\rENG} run on, you know, when they go offline, that, that's it they're gone forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.00,0:12:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我认为这很糟糕。 \N {\rENG} And I think that kind of sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:32.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，我完全同意。 \N {\rENG} Yeah, I fully agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:36.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的意思是，在一步步进入软件开发之后，我 \N {\rENG} I mean, having gotten into software development, step by step, I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,可以迈出第一步，用 HTML、CSS 构建一个小东西， \N {\rENG} could take my first steps with building a little thing with HTML,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.00,0:12:43.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后一步一步地，你想让它更实用、更真实。 \N {\rENG} CSS and step by step, you want to make it more functional, more real.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.00,0:12:48.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后你开始拉动这条线，就像所有的复杂性都 \N {\rENG} And then you start pulling on that thread, like all that complexity comes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.00,0:12:50.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,向你袭来，而且永无止境。 \N {\rENG} towards you and it's never ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.00,0:12:56.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,因此，需要学习的东西太多，需要维护的东西太多，需要支付和操作的东西太多。 \N {\rENG} So it's so much to learn, so much to maintain, so much to pay for and operate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.00,0:13:00.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我希望有一种更简单的方法来构建和运行事物。 \N {\rENG} So I wish there was a simpler way to, to build things and to run things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.00,0:13:05.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以也许这是一个很好的问题，什么是本地第一？ \N {\rENG} So maybe this is a good point to ask, what is local first?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.00,0:13:06.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么是本地优先？ \N {\rENG} What is Local First?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.00,0:13:11.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,本地优先软件是在您的计算机上运行并 \N {\rENG} local-first software is software that runs on your computer and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.00,0:13:12.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,与其他人协作的软件。 \N {\rENG} collaborates with other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.00,0:13:16.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们认为云最重要的是协作。 \N {\rENG} We think that the most important thing about the cloud is collaboration.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.00,0:13:20.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这种无处不在、随时可访问的数据副本可以从任何地方获取。 \N {\rENG} This ubiquitous, always accessible, copy of your data from anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.00,0:13:23.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,您可以向某人发送链接，然后你们就可以立即合作。 \N {\rENG} You can send someone a link and you're working together right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.00,0:13:25.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,无需下载，无需安装。 \N {\rENG} Nothing to download, nothing to install.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.00,0:13:29.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,但云的缺点是您实际上没有该软件。 \N {\rENG} But the downside of the cloud is that you don't actually have the software.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.00,0:13:34.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,因此，我们认为您应该拥有计算机上的程序和数据的副本 \N {\rENG} And so what we think you should have is a copy of the program and the data on your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.00,0:13:38.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,，但它仍然应该能够与其他人协作，对吗？ \N {\rENG} computer, but it should still be able to collaborate with other people, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.00,0:13:41.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们希望将云的优点与 \N {\rENG} We want the good parts of the cloud combined with the good
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:43.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,旧构建方式的优点结合起来。 \N {\rENG} parts of the old way of building.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.00,0:13:48.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在某种程度上，现在我们有很棒的协作工具，如 \N {\rENG} And in a way right now we have great collaboration tools like
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.00,0:13:51.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,Google Drive 和 Figma 等。 \N {\rENG} Google Drive and Figma, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.00,0:13:54.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,但默认情况下，这些工具都存储在云端。 \N {\rENG} But it's all by default lives in the cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.00,0:13:59.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以你建议让我们鱼与熊掌兼得，这样软件就可以 \N {\rENG} So you suggesting let's have the cake and eat it too, so that the software
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.00,0:14:05.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在客户端上完全运行，我们只使用服务器来完成绝对必要的 \N {\rENG} fully works on the client and we only use the server for the absolutely necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.00,0:14:09.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,部分，但仍然可以进行协作。 \N {\rENG} pieces but still have collaboration.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.00,0:14:09.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是正确的。 \N {\rENG} That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.00,0:14:14.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,道格·恩格尔巴特（Doug Engelbart），你知道，一位著名的计算机科学研究 \N {\rENG} And Doug Engelbart, you know, a famous computer science
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.00,0:14:20.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,人员，他谈到了我们如何增强我们的智力。 \N {\rENG} researcher he talked about how we can de- augment our intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.00,0:14:23.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们可能会让事情变得更糟。 \N {\rENG} We can make things worse for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.00,0:14:27.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,他通过将一块砖头粘在铅笔上 \N {\rENG} And he demonstrated this really poetically by taping a brick to a pencil
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.00,0:14:29.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,并要求人们用它写字来真正诗意地展示了这一点。 \N {\rENG} and asking people to write with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.00,0:14:33.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我并不是说解决这些技术问题一定有免费午餐 \N {\rENG} So I'm not here to say that there are free lunches necessarily in solving these
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.00,0:14:37.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,，但我确实认为我们可能已经在铅笔上贴了一些巨大的砖块 \N {\rENG} technical problems, but I do think that we may have taped a few giant bricks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.00,0:14:41.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,，并且我们已经解决了很多不必要的困难。 \N {\rENG} to our pencils here, and that there's a lot of unnecessary difficulty that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.00,0:14:47.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,通过选择不太适合该任务的架构来引入。 \N {\rENG} we've introduced by picking architectures that are not well suited to the task.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.00,0:14:49.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在很多情况下，这些都是伟大的技术。 \N {\rENG} These are in many cases, great technologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.00,0:14:53.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,只是我们正在部署与 \N {\rENG} It's just that we're deploying the same technology that we would use to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.00,0:14:58.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,构建 10 亿人应用程序相同的技术来构建10 人应用程序或 100 万人应用程序。 \N {\rENG} build a billion person app to build a 10 person app or a million person app.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.00,0:15:01.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,而且要求完全不同。 \N {\rENG} And the requirements are just radically different.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.00,0:15:08.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在，我认为这种技术堆栈的同质化是 \N {\rENG} Now, I think this sort of homogenization of the technical stack is part of why
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.00,0:15:10.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们所处位置的部分原因。 \N {\rENG} we're in the position that we're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.00,0:15:13.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像乔纳森·爱德华兹（Jonathan Edwards）所说的那样，你知道，我们被 \N {\rENG} Like Jonathan Edwards famously said, you know, we were
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:15.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,承诺为心灵提供自行车。 \N {\rENG} promised bicycles for the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.00,0:15:18.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,但他们却给了我们航空母舰，对吗？ \N {\rENG} But they gave us aircraft carriers instead, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.00,0:15:23.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以，当我们需要自行车时，我们正在建造航空母舰。 \N {\rENG} So, so we're building aircraft carriers when we need bicycles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.00,0:15:25.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这并不意味着航空母舰没有用处。 \N {\rENG} That doesn't mean that the aircraft carrier isn't useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.00,0:15:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你需要像美国海军一样在南太平洋投射兵力，它非常有用， \N {\rENG} It's very useful if you need to project force in the South Pacific as the U.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.00,0:15:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,- \N {\rENG} S.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.00,0:15:35.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,但如果你想去买杂货，它就没有多大帮助了。 \N {\rENG} Navy, but it's not terribly helpful if you want to go get groceries.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.00,0:15:35.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,正确的？ \N {\rENG} Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.00,0:15:37.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是不适合这项工作的工具。 \N {\rENG} It's the wrong tool for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.00,0:15:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们只是尝试用一套工具完成所有事情。 \N {\rENG} And we're just trying to do everything with one set of tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.00,0:15:44.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,因此，您提到它基本上应该在没有服务器的情况下在我们的设备上完全运行， \N {\rENG} So you've mentioned that it basically should work fully on our device
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.00,0:15:48.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,并且服务器通过提供 \N {\rENG} without the server and the server augments that software by giving
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.00,0:15:52.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,附加功能（例如协作）来增强该软件，也许它还有助于 \N {\rENG} it additional capabilities, such as collaboration, maybe it also helps
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.00,0:15:55.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,自动备份等。 \N {\rENG} with automatic backup, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.00,0:15:56.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,以便。 \N {\rENG} So, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.00,0:15:57.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,非常清楚。 \N {\rENG} is very clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.00,0:16:01.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,然而，目前还不是很清楚我将如何从通常 \N {\rENG} However, it would not be super clear yet how I would go from typically
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.00,0:16:06.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,构建一个三层 Web 应用程序转向在该模型中构建事物。 \N {\rENG} building a three tier web app to building things in that model.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.00,0:16:11.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的直觉可能是添加大量缓存，等等。 \N {\rENG} My intuition would be maybe adding tons of caching, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.00,0:16:14.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还会拥有该服务器数据库吗？ \N {\rENG} Would I still have that server database?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.00,0:16:17.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,那么我构建本地优先应用程序的典型方法是什么？ \N {\rENG} So what is the typical way how I built local first apps?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.00,0:16:19.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，你有两个主要问题。 \N {\rENG} Yeah, you kind of have two main problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.00,0:16:21.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,有程序和数据，对吗？ \N {\rENG} There's the program and the data, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.00,0:16:23.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们将其简单化。 \N {\rENG} We'll just kind of boil it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:26.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,程序在某种意义上是容易解决的问题。 \N {\rENG} The program in some sense is the easy problem to solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.00,0:16:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以，你知道，如果你在网络上，你想要的是一个 PWA，渐进式网络应用程序。 \N {\rENG} So, you know, if you're on the web, what you want is a PWA, progressive web app.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.00,0:16:34.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,您将使用服务工作线程来缓存代码。 \N {\rENG} You're going to use a service worker to cache the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.00,0:16:37.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,您将尝试在浏览器中运行所有内容，并且将 \N {\rENG} You're going to try and run everything in the browser, and you're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.00,0:16:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,其存储起来，以便它可以离线工作。 \N {\rENG} keep it stored so it works offline.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.00,0:16:44.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果您使用移动设备，在很多情况下您已经以这种方式进行构建， \N {\rENG} If you're on mobile, in many cases you already build this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.00,0:16:45.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的。 \N {\rENG} Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.00,0:16:49.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像苹果公司或多或少发布的第一方发布的所有内容一样。 \N {\rENG} Like, everything that Apple publishes first party, more or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.00,0:16:51.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,已经是本地优先了吧？ \N {\rENG} Is already local first, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.00,0:16:52.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像苹果笔记一样。 \N {\rENG} Like Apple notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.00,0:16:56.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不会在电梯里拿出手机来 \N {\rENG} It's not like you ever pull out your phone in the elevator to, like, make a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.00,0:16:58.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,记下刚刚的谈话。 \N {\rENG} note from a conversation you just had.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.00,0:16:59.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你所看到的只是一个小旋转器。 \N {\rENG} And all you see is a little spinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.00,0:17:01.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，这太荒谬了，对吧？ \N {\rENG} No, that's ridiculous, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.00,0:17:02.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像苹果笔记那样， \N {\rENG} Like Apple Notes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:06.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我认为苹果笔记是应用程序应该是什么样的一个很好的例子，而 \N {\rENG} I think Apple notes is a great example of what an app should feel like, whereas
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.00,0:17:10.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很多时候在走廊上看到那个旋转器，而我 \N {\rENG} I do a lot of times see that spinner on the hallway where I don't have perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.00,0:17:13.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在其他应用程序中没有完美的互联网连接。 \N {\rENG} internet connectivity in other apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.00,0:17:13.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,正确的？ \N {\rENG} right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.00,0:17:15.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为您在某人的办公室，并且想要记录一些 \N {\rENG} Because you're at somebody's office and you know, want to make some notes about a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.00,0:17:18.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,不在 WiFi 或其他设备上进行的对话记录。 \N {\rENG} conversation not on the WiFi or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:19.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你会想，天哪，我需要 \N {\rENG} And you're like, Oh, God, I gotta
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.00,0:17:21.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,wifi 密码吗？ \N {\rENG} wiFi password?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.00,0:17:22.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，不，这太荒谬了。 \N {\rENG} Yeah, no, that's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.00,0:17:24.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是想在这里做个笔记。 \N {\rENG} I'm just trying to take a note here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.00,0:17:26.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，那么，您需要在设备上获取该程序。 \N {\rENG} Okay, so, so you need to get the program on the device.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:27.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是一个。 \N {\rENG} That's one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.00,0:17:29.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后你需要获取设备上的数据。 \N {\rENG} And then you need to get the data on the device.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.00,0:17:30.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,那也是。 \N {\rENG} That's too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.00,0:17:32.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,那么如何获取设备上的数据呢？ \N {\rENG} So how do you get the data on the device?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.00,0:17:36.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，在某些非常有限的情况下，您只需将数据放入程序中，对吗？ \N {\rENG} Well, in some very limited cases, you just put the data into the program, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.00,0:17:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以，我不知道，也许这是棋盘 \N {\rENG} So like, I don't know, maybe it's a reference for a board
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.00,0:17:41.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,游戏或类似游戏的参考。 \N {\rENG} game or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.00,0:17:45.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,您只需下载数据并将其留在应用程序中即可。 \N {\rENG} You can just download the data and leave it in the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.00,0:17:47.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,但当然，这并不像这个有趣的案例。 \N {\rENG} But of course, that's not like the interesting case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.00,0:17:51.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想，很多应用程序，大多数应用程序，都有用户生成的内容。 \N {\rENG} A lot of apps, most apps, I think, you know, you have user generated content.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:52.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就是你在那儿的原因，对吧？ \N {\rENG} That's why you're there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:55.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,它是一张地图，它是一个笔记，它是您在那里要做的任何事情。 \N {\rENG} It's a map, it's a note, it's whatever you're there to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.00,0:17:58.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这种情况下，您需要什么。 \N {\rENG} And so in that case, what you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.00,0:18:02.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是一种将数据从云端获取到设备然后返回云端的方法。 \N {\rENG} Is some way to get data from the cloud to the device and then back to the cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.00,0:18:07.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,棘手的部分是你需要处理人们可以离线的事实。 \N {\rENG} And the tricky part is you need to deal with the fact that people can go offline.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:12.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以这些数据基本上是我之前创建的一些数据。 \N {\rENG} And so that data is basically some data I might've previously created.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.00,0:18:16.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,例如，如果它是 Apple笔记应用程序，那么可能是 \N {\rENG} For example, if it's the Apple notes app, then maybe some notes
